timelineItems.desc:
From pre-match arm-wrestling against Viking Jesus, to taking in an epic tailgate, to a full 90 of singing and dancing, Rachel dives in to the match day experience with the South Ward, New York Red Bulls' collective of passionate supporters.

"Get Me In There" is a 10-part series, presented by Heineken, bringing you an inside look at the fans that drum, dance, sing, tailgate, and do whatever it takes to create the most dynamic match day atmospheres in Major League Soccer.

Watch Episode 1 here: mlssoccer.com/video/2015/06/23/wheels-bus-get-me-there-episode-1


Tweet at Rachel (@rachelbonnetta) using the hashtag #SoccerIsHere and let us know where we should go next!

MLSsoccer.com's Katie Witham and Calen Carr, former Houston Dynamo forward, report from the Steve Nash Foundation Showdown in New York City. The annual event brings together the best in the world of professional soccer and professional basketball to benefit the Steve Nash Foundation. 

Katie and Calen talk to Steve Nash, Geoff Cameron, Stu Holden, Luol Deng and more.
